# Test hex2 ~ and ! operators with a LARGE displacement (> 4096 bytes)
# This tests the case where hi20 is non-zero (auipc loads a page offset).
# Strategy: place data far away (>4K from code), load it, check value.
#
# Code at 0x240, data at 0x1280 (offset 0x1040 = 4160 from auipc).
# hi20 = ((4160 + 0x800) >> 12) = (0x1840 >> 12) = 1
# lo12 = 4160 - (1 << 12) = 4160 - 4096 = 64 = 0x40
# But with !label: disp = 0x1280 - 0x244 = 0x103C, lo12 = (0x103C+4)&0xFFF = 0x040
#
# PE header: SizeOfCode=0x1080, SizeOfImage=0x12C0
